    <item>
      <title>Rust implementation of K-Means</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/k-means/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 17 Nov 2024 09:45:49 +0100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/k-means/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;I got an assignment for this week: write the K-Means algorithm, in any language you like. &lt;br&gt;&#xA;So, first, we have to understand what it does and how it works.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-k-means&#34;&gt;What is K-Means?&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;k-means clustering is a method of vector quantization, originally from signal processing, that aims to partition n observations into k clusters in which each observation belongs to the cluster with the nearest mean (cluster centers or cluster centroid), serving as a prototype of the cluster. &lt;sup&gt;[1]&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
